  "text": "The high-copy composite vectors were constructed following a previously described approach [CITATION_1] . The highcopy composite BAC vector pHZAUBAC1 was constructed by ligating the low-copy BAC vector pIndigo-BAC536-S to the high-copy pGEM-4Z at the HindIII site, and was selected on LB medium containing chloramphenicol (12.5 μg/mL), ampicillin (50 μg/mL), X-gal (80 μg/mL) and IPTG (100 μg/mL). The high-copy composite BIBAC vector pHZAUBIBAC1 was constructed by ligating the low-copy BIBAC-S to the high-copy pGEM-4Z at the BamHI site, and was selected on LB medium containing kanamycin (20 μg/mL), ampicillin (50 μg/mL), X-gal (80 μg/mL) and IPTG (100 μg/mL). All resulting colonies were to be blue.",
